This is the actual South Pacific program

26:18.329 --> 26:19.895
from Camp Canyon Grove? Look at that.

26:20.162 --> 26:23.633
- Where did you get this?
- I saved it this whole time.

26:24.768 --> 26:27.035
Okay, actually, I bought it on eBay.

26:27.060 --> 26:29.093
People sell, like, everything there.

26:29.436 --> 26:30.809
But I thought it'd be

26:30.834 --> 26:32.967
a nice thing for you to sign.

26:32.992 --> 26:34.850
Really?

26:36.151 --> 26:38.117
Okay.

26:38.142 --> 26:40.643
Oh, my God, this is so sweet.

26:43.154 --> 26:44.258
Thank you.

26:45.366 --> 26:47.866
You are really always there
when I need someone.

26:51.433 --> 26:53.466
- I guess I'll sign, like, right here?
- Awesome.

26:58.691 --> 26:59.957
Thanks.

27:04.244 --> 27:06.244
Oh.

27:06.269 --> 27:07.969
Hi, hey, there.

27:07.994 --> 27:09.832
- Hi.
- Hi, how are you?

27:09.857 --> 27:11.091
Um...

27:11.116 --> 27:12.494
Oh, what's happening?

27:12.518 --> 27:13.538
I just want to let you know

27:13.563 --> 27:16.062
that I did get another offer.

27:16.927 --> 27:18.088
Oh.

27:18.156 --> 27:19.623
Okay, I see.

27:19.735 --> 27:21.535
Well, thank you for letting me know.

27:21.560 --> 27:22.826
And...

27:22.903 --> 27:26.395
- was our offer competitive?
- Well... this...

27:26.907 --> 27:28.522
is their opening bid.

27:28.634 --> 27:30.100
Holy macaroni.

27:30.212 --> 27:34.114
- Wow, that is, um, some major scratch.
- Yeah.

27:34.139 --> 27:35.972
I know, I mean, money like that could...

27:35.997 --> 27:37.463
mean so much to my family.

27:37.488 --> 27:39.920
We could get out of debt,
could pay off the house.

27:39.945 --> 27:42.619
Tommy wants to go to college. College.

27:42.644 --> 27:46.574
I mean, our highest dream for him
was, you know, like a six-week course

27:46.599 --> 27:47.828
in welding, so...

27:47.853 --> 27:49.719
So, wait, so what are you saying?

27:49.832 --> 27:52.443
I don't know if I'm gonna work with...

27:52.468 --> 27:55.150
this exact firm, but
it turns out that...

27:56.862 --> 27:58.361
this is what I'm worth.

28:02.458 --> 28:03.844
Okay, um...

28:04.322 --> 28:06.543
- I'll see you in there.
- Yeah.

28:06.568 --> 28:08.238
- All right?
- Mm-hmm.

28:08.351 --> 28:10.727
Okay. It's good to see you.

28:10.752 --> 28:12.619
Thank you. Good to see you.

28:14.613 --> 28:16.346
All right, everyone. Showtime, showtime!

28:16.415 --> 28:17.814
But, you know, break a leg.

28:17.883 --> 28:19.636
Now, Rebecca. I want you to remember

28:19.661 --> 28:22.462
to shimmy, shake, and smile, okay?

28:22.487 --> 28:24.399
I want to see both rows
of teeth. Top and bottom.

28:25.042 --> 28:26.400
Where's my tea?

28:26.853 --> 28:28.753
Well, where is it?!

28:31.477 --> 28:33.407
Check this out.

28:33.432 --> 28:36.387
This, like, totally suits me.

28:36.412 --> 28:39.179
Anyone seeing this won't
be oblivious anymore.

28:39.212 --> 28:41.159
- Right?
- Uh-huh.

28:41.826 --> 28:42.826
Okay.

28:49.058 --> 28:51.291
♪ When he came to my town ♪

28:51.316 --> 28:53.227
♪ Upon his ship ♪

28:53.252 --> 28:56.654
♪ He pillaged and plundered and looted ♪

28:57.480 --> 28:58.846
♪ "You're mine now," he said ♪

28:58.890 --> 29:00.757
♪ With a devilish grin ♪

29:00.826 --> 29:04.864
♪ "Submit, or be executed" ♪

29:04.889 --> 29:06.106
♪ Yet now that ♪

29:06.131 --> 29:08.498
♪ I'm his bride ♪

29:08.781 --> 29:12.816
♪ I feel nothing but
warmth deep inside ♪

29:14.406 --> 29:18.208
♪ I love the Pirate King ♪

29:18.276 --> 29:19.576
♪ I sit on his lap ♪

29:19.689 --> 29:21.488
♪ And to him I sing ♪

29:21.513 --> 29:23.580
♪ He calls me his sparrow ♪

29:23.649 --> 29:25.615
♪ His lamb, his pet ♪

29:25.728 --> 29:27.561
♪ His rough pirate kisses ♪

29:27.586 --> 29:29.786
♪ I'll never forget ♪

29:29.855 --> 29:33.487
♪ He hits me but he
don't mean no harm ♪

29:33.512 --> 29:35.742
♪ Those slaps are part of his ♪

29:35.767 --> 29:38.601
♪ Piratish charm ♪

29:40.095 --> 29:41.656
♪ Sometimes I say ♪

29:41.672 --> 29:43.172
♪ "Stop it," but deep down ♪

29:43.240 --> 29:44.406
♪ I know ♪

29:44.475 --> 29:45.741
♪ If I didn't like it ♪

29:45.766 --> 29:48.550
♪ I would have left long ago... ♪

29:48.822 --> 29:51.044
That pirate sounds like a dick.

29:51.069 --> 29:53.703
♪ I love the Pirate King ♪

29:54.118 --> 29:56.986
♪ He calls my name and it means ♪

29:57.011 --> 29:58.050
♪ One thing ♪

29:58.075 --> 29:59.674
♪ He's craving my touch ♪

30:00.124 --> 30:01.790
♪ Warm and deep ♪

30:01.859 --> 30:03.659
♪ He takes his pleasure ♪

30:03.728 --> 30:05.160
♪ Even when I'm asleep ♪

30:05.466 --> 30:07.540
♪ If I die at his hand ♪

30:07.565 --> 30:09.898
♪ It won't be a surprise ♪

30:09.947 --> 30:13.219
♪ 'Cause my love
for the Pirate King ♪

30:13.244 --> 30:15.558
♪ Is true and pure ♪

30:15.583 --> 30:18.818
♪ And wise. ♪

30:21.612 --> 30:22.612
Yeah.

30:31.310 --> 30:34.056
You were great. You know,

30:34.081 --> 30:36.014
if I were a pirate king,
I'd kidnap you, too.

30:37.361 --> 30:39.061
And would you marry me?

30:39.130 --> 30:41.263
Hmm. I mean, I'd be a pirate king,

30:41.288 --> 30:43.055
so I just would do what I want.

30:43.080 --> 30:44.280
You don't understand anything.

30:44.357 --> 30:45.768
You don't even understand
you're not supposed

30:45.793 --> 30:47.370
to come back here in
the middle of a show.

30:47.676 --> 30:50.696
You know, I think
something's going on with us.

30:50.721 --> 30:52.254
You're mad at me.

30:52.279 --> 30:54.913
I can tell from the
yelling and overt anger.

30:55.113 --> 30:57.261
Wow. Amazing.

30:57.286 --> 30:58.586
You're not only a pirate king...

30:58.724 --> 31:00.624
you're a genius.

31:05.012 --> 31:07.846
Oh, God, this next
song is a total bummer.

31:07.871 --> 31:10.138
It's one of the ones
that just lifts right out.

31:12.496 --> 31:14.386
Oh, hello there, folks.

31:14.455 --> 31:15.887
I didn't see you there.

31:15.956 --> 31:19.399
My name is not important,

31:19.424 --> 31:22.335
but there's something about
me that you should know.

31:22.663 --> 31:25.697
♪ I'm an apple man ♪

31:25.722 --> 31:28.623
♪ I'm an apple man ♪

31:28.648 --> 31:32.383
♪ No other fruit can do
quite what an apple can ♪

31:32.539 --> 31:34.372
♪ Toss me that apple, Stan ♪

31:34.397 --> 31:37.065
♪ 'Cause I'm an apple man ♪

31:38.579 --> 31:40.612
♪ They're marvelous in the morning ♪

31:40.681 --> 31:43.215
♪ They're lovely late at night ♪

31:43.283 --> 31:46.184
♪ They're delectable
in the daytime ♪

31:46.286 --> 31:48.120
♪ An apple always
tastes just right ♪

31:48.188 --> 31:50.731
♪ So you can keep your banana ♪

31:50.756 --> 31:53.302
♪ In your pineapple cabana ♪

31:53.327 --> 31:55.761
♪ I'd never be caught
chomping on a kumquat ♪

31:55.786 --> 31:58.373
♪ Tell that to your
friend Susannah ♪

31:58.398 --> 32:01.066
♪ From Tallahassee to Spokane ♪

32:01.091 --> 32:03.479
♪ Madagascar to Japan ♪

32:03.504 --> 32:05.971
♪ I'm sticking to
my one-fruit plan ♪

32:05.996 --> 32:09.716
♪ 'Cause I'm a Gala, Red
Delicious, Cortland, Fuji ♪

32:09.777 --> 32:12.244
♪ McIntosh, Granny Smith, Ambrosia ♪

32:12.312 --> 32:14.579
♪ Apple man. ♪

32:18.240 --> 32:19.606
That is it, April.

32:19.953 --> 32:21.286
I'm an apple man.

32:21.606 --> 32:23.232
Paula is my apple,

32:23.257 --> 32:24.817
and I need to try new fruit but I can't,

32:24.858 --> 32:27.684
because I'm afraid of
all the change at work.

32:27.709 --> 32:29.839
Nathaniel came in and Karen left,

32:29.864 --> 32:31.540
and then Bert came in and Jim left.

32:31.565 --> 32:33.298
And then he came back
and then Rebecca left.

32:33.323 --> 32:34.731
And through it all,

32:35.090 --> 32:38.224
Paula has been there, and
that's why I'm so upset.

32:38.405 --> 32:41.339
Y-You got all of that from "Apple Man"?

32:41.364 --> 32:42.897
Yes, of course.

32:43.159 --> 32:45.888
But you didn't get it from the
song, "Good Bosses and Friends

32:45.913 --> 32:48.446
Let Their Employees Soar
Elsewhere If Need Be"?

32:48.515 --> 32:50.751
No, I, I didn't connect with that one.

32:56.223 --> 32:58.382
Hey. You ready?

32:59.170 --> 33:00.945
I don't think I can sing this song.

33:01.961 --> 33:03.662
I hate my song.

33:03.774 --> 33:05.207
No, I hate everything about it.

33:05.232 --> 33:07.833
I-I hate, I hate what it's
about and what it says.

33:07.858 --> 33:09.792
Come on, it's just one
dumb song. Who cares?

33:09.903 --> 33:11.002
No, you don't understand.

33:11.027 --> 33:13.327
Loving these songs
is a part of who I am.

33:13.352 --> 33:14.985
I don't know, I just,

33:15.142 --> 33:17.868
I liked what I wrote, I
like the changes that I made.

33:18.720 --> 33:22.480
Then why not sing that version instead?

33:22.505 --> 33:25.001
I can't. You heard
Connie. She hated that.

33:26.039 --> 33:28.730
And I can't even
believe that I did that.

33:28.755 --> 33:30.388
I mean, God, I'm not
a writer-performer.

33:30.413 --> 33:32.455
I'm not Ike Barinholtz.

33:34.541 --> 33:36.875
Hey, Rebecca, you're on.

33:37.974 --> 33:39.741
I don't know, I just
wish that the audience

33:39.766 --> 33:41.077
could hear the lyrics that I wrote,

33:41.101 --> 33:43.435
but I, I can't go out
there and sing them.

33:43.503 --> 33:44.776
They should hear them.

33:46.019 --> 33:47.235
And they will.

33:51.533 --> 33:52.589
What?

33:55.159 --> 33:56.425
Hello, everybody,

33:56.450 --> 33:58.304
um, instead of singing the prince song,

33:58.329 --> 34:01.163
I'm actually gonna sing a
different song with a few

34:01.188 --> 34:04.241
small changes made by a, uh,

34:04.969 --> 34:06.049
a brilliant friend of mine.

34:09.639 --> 34:13.275
♪ I'm the local
lady of the evening ♪

34:13.300 --> 34:16.701
♪ And though I like
my men and my booze ♪

34:16.726 --> 34:19.348
♪ I pray to above ♪

34:19.373 --> 34:21.027
♪ That I'll find true love ♪

34:21.052 --> 34:23.452
♪ A man who won't
say that I'm used ♪

34:23.476 --> 34:25.744
- Oh, my God.
- ♪ Oh, can someone ♪

34:25.812 --> 34:28.580
- Someone else is singing my song.
- ♪ Lasso me a husband? ♪

34:28.649 --> 34:30.460
♪ It would be nice to
someday have a husband... ♪

34:30.484 --> 34:33.179
Close the curtain. Close the curtain.

34:35.866 --> 34:37.466
Connie, listen...

34:37.491 --> 34:38.920
- You're fired.
- What?

34:38.945 --> 34:40.375
Both of you, you're fired.

34:40.400 --> 34:42.000
Now get out of my theater at once.

34:51.458 --> 34:53.726
Well, big surprise, no one's coming.

34:53.751 --> 34:56.482
No one in this god-awful
town is coming here.

34:56.873 --> 34:58.197
Will you just hold on a second?

34:58.222 --> 34:59.855
We don't even open for five minutes.

35:01.826 --> 35:03.079
Table for two, please?

35:03.104 --> 35:05.404
Ah, we've got two.

35:05.429 --> 35:06.861
Two people. Big deal.

35:06.974 --> 35:10.075
Hi. Oh, you've got four.

35:10.440 --> 35:13.089
- Hi.
- Hi, welcome.

35:13.114 --> 35:15.581
Hi. Yeah, you can sit there.

35:15.650 --> 35:17.650
Um, Greg, there are,
like, eight people here.

35:17.718 --> 35:19.418
It's just like the old Serrano's.

35:19.443 --> 35:20.796
Uh, ten top. Incoming.

35:20.821 --> 35:23.989
Kitchen, start your engines,
these people are early.

35:24.102 --> 35:25.501
Why don't you guys sit right there?

35:25.526 --> 35:26.959
Man, I have missed this place.

35:27.028 --> 35:28.494
I cannot believe it.

35:28.562 --> 35:31.575
If this were a real opening,
we would've done huge numbers.

35:31.600 --> 35:32.359
Mm-hmm.

35:32.392 --> 35:34.999
It's like people
actually like this place.

35:35.024 --> 35:36.811
Dude, you don't get it. They always did.

35:36.836 --> 35:39.115
It's just, when your father
ran this place, he was a drunk

35:39.140 --> 35:42.274
and a terrible businessman
and he ran it into the ground.

35:42.299 --> 35:43.932
No, this place failed
because West Covina

35:43.957 --> 35:45.556
turned their back on this restaurant.

35:45.581 --> 35:47.981
That's one of the reasons
why I hated it here.

35:48.006 --> 35:50.559
Yeah, that's not true. You
just wanted to find reasons

35:50.584 --> 35:52.770
to hate it because you hated yourself.

35:54.062 --> 35:56.029
Trust me, I dated you. It was not cute.

35:56.467 --> 35:58.734
- Huh.
- I mean, the good news is,

35:58.759 --> 36:00.426
you used that hatred and,

36:00.451 --> 36:02.515
parenthetically, your horrible
relationship with Rebecca,

36:02.540 --> 36:04.974
to get out of town and
go to business school.

36:04.999 --> 36:07.800
So maybe now you're ready for this town.

36:08.901 --> 36:10.667
It's always been ready for you.

36:10.911 --> 36:12.183
Wow.

36:13.040 --> 36:15.178
I forgot how profound you are.

36:15.203 --> 36:17.721
That is always a big mistake.

36:35.894 --> 36:37.160
Huh.

36:48.863 --> 36:50.796
Still got it.

36:52.165 --> 36:56.381
♪ Hey, West Covina ♪

36:56.450 --> 36:59.867
♪ Thought that I had to break free ♪

37:00.799 --> 37:05.334
♪ Well, it took me two
years to shake off my fears ♪

37:05.359 --> 37:09.721
♪ And see that the problem was me ♪

37:09.964 --> 37:13.966
♪ Hey, West Covina ♪

37:14.351 --> 37:17.703
♪ We may not always agree ♪

37:18.364 --> 37:20.598
♪ But you're okay, West Covina ♪

37:20.841 --> 37:23.881
♪ Should I stay, West Covina? ♪

37:24.178 --> 37:27.546
♪ What do you say, West Covina? ♪

37:28.063 --> 37:33.006
♪ What'll it be? ♪

37:34.789 --> 37:40.374
♪ Hmm. ♪

37:44.665 --> 37:46.431
I am so sorry that I got you fired.

37:46.500 --> 37:47.866
No, it's okay.

37:48.001 --> 37:49.635
If I'm being honest...

37:50.571 --> 37:52.571
I only did this to hang out with you.

37:54.208 --> 37:55.307
Oh, wow.

37:55.709 --> 37:57.670
Are you really surprised to hear that?

37:59.764 --> 38:01.113
Kind of?

38:01.894 --> 38:02.792
Nathaniel, what you just did

38:02.817 --> 38:05.114
meant a lot to me, really.

38:06.135 --> 38:07.148
It was thrilling

38:07.173 --> 38:10.560
to hear my words out loud,
even if it was a dumb idea.

38:11.237 --> 38:13.171
I don't think it was dumb.

38:15.464 --> 38:16.663
Really?

38:25.372 --> 38:27.973
Uh, we should, uh... yeah. I
should... no, I should get my stuff.

38:51.060 --> 38:52.592
Hey.

38:54.474 --> 38:57.303
You need to take one
of those great offers, Paula.

38:57.328 --> 38:59.128
- I know.
- It took one of the songs

38:59.153 --> 39:01.153
last night for me to realize that.

39:01.178 --> 39:03.157
Was it the one called "Money
Isn't Everything Unless It Gets

39:03.182 --> 39:05.667
Your Family Out Of Debt And
Sends Your Kid To College"?

39:05.692 --> 39:09.060
No, I-I didn't vibe with that one.

39:09.085 --> 39:11.252
I, I shouldn't have
tried to hold you here.

39:11.375 --> 39:13.420
Just because you mean so much to me.

39:13.445 --> 39:16.270
Ah, Darryl, come on.

39:17.321 --> 39:18.921
We are friends.

39:19.107 --> 39:22.409
Real friends, not "work friends."

39:22.434 --> 39:26.169
And we will be in each
other's lives forever.

39:27.308 --> 39:29.608
No matter where we get our paycheck.

39:30.368 --> 39:31.516
Really?

39:34.136 --> 39:35.427
Hell, yeah.

39:44.305 --> 39:45.705
Hey. Thank you for coming.

39:45.738 --> 39:46.557
Yeah.

39:47.535 --> 39:49.201
I have something to tell you.

39:49.599 --> 39:51.966
Okay.

39:52.114 --> 39:54.181
I want to get married.

39:54.797 --> 39:56.900
Everyone I grew up with is married.

39:56.925 --> 39:58.436
I've planned a billion
weddings for people

39:58.461 --> 40:00.661
who love each other a
lot less than you and I do

40:00.686 --> 40:02.286
and aren't as attractive as we are.

40:02.422 --> 40:04.007
I want this.

40:04.420 --> 40:05.853
I want you to propose, Beth.

40:06.502 --> 40:08.168
And if you don't,

40:08.575 --> 40:10.495
then I'm not going back
to New York with you.

40:20.282 --> 40:21.679
Hey.

40:22.073 --> 40:23.558
What are you doing here?

40:23.583 --> 40:25.389
Well, since I missed
your opening, I wanted

40:25.414 --> 40:29.192
to check the place
out, and... oh, my God.

40:29.323 --> 40:31.556
Greg, this looks amazing.

40:31.581 --> 40:33.214
Yeah. Thanks.

40:33.581 --> 40:34.791
I'm sorry I missed your theater thing.

40:34.816 --> 40:36.649
- How was it?
- Oh, it was terrible.

40:36.946 --> 40:39.859
Yeah, uh, yeah, I got yelled
at, I got called an idiot

40:39.884 --> 40:41.249
and then I got fired.

40:41.274 --> 40:43.474
Wow. That sucks.

40:43.499 --> 40:45.210
Yeah, I mean, there were some
good parts, there were actually

40:45.235 --> 40:50.519
some really good parts,
but mostly, I, uh,

40:50.829 --> 40:53.103
- I got my dreams stomped on.
- Oh.

40:53.387 --> 40:55.954
But enough about me. Look at you.

40:55.979 --> 40:58.779
Really. You look so happy,
you're, like, glowing.

40:58.804 --> 41:01.151
I feel pretty good, actually,

41:01.176 --> 41:03.810
and I-I decided, um,

41:04.186 --> 41:07.621
I'm gonna stay in town
and really open this place.

41:07.689 --> 41:09.122
Try to make it work.

41:09.147 --> 41:10.217
Wow.

41:10.242 --> 41:11.875
You're choosing to stay in West Covina?

41:11.917 --> 41:13.383
- By choice?
- Yes,

41:13.408 --> 41:15.168
and when I made that
decision, I had to ask myself,

41:15.193 --> 41:16.293
was it because of you

41:16.318 --> 41:17.584
or because of this place?

41:17.609 --> 41:20.176
Because of me? Why because of me?

41:20.740 --> 41:22.606
Because I still care about you.

41:23.403 --> 41:25.011
And maybe I did choose

41:25.036 --> 41:27.370
to do my thesis here to be
near you, but now I really,

41:27.395 --> 41:29.112
I, I love this restaurant.

41:29.878 --> 41:32.312
Good. Well, good, good.

41:32.337 --> 41:36.424
That is, that's good...
That's good. That's great.

41:36.449 --> 41:37.882
Wait, are you hungry?

41:37.907 --> 41:39.373
You got to try this lasagna.

41:39.398 --> 41:40.965
I was using Roma, but Chris was right,

41:40.990 --> 41:42.845
the San Marzano was
better, so I switched.

41:42.870 --> 41:44.303
Just, hold on.

41:44.583 --> 41:46.550
You're gonna love it.

41:47.022 --> 41:48.697
Oh.

41:50.788 --> 41:52.888
♪ Oh, can someone ♪

41:52.913 --> 41:56.214
♪ Lasso me a husband? ♪

42:01.701 --> 42:02.801
Damn it.

